.TH MYBTRFS-STATS 1 "June 2026" "mybtrfs 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
mybtrfs-stats \- show aggregate backup statistics (snapshot/backup counts, sizes, space savings)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mybtrfs stats
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
\fISNAP_DIR TARGET\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mybtrfs stats
displays aggregate statistics about snapshots and backups:
.TP
\(bu
Total count of snapshots and backups
.TP
\(bu
Total size of snapshots and backups
.TP
\(bu
Disk usage on source and target filesystems
.TP
\(bu
Space savings from deduplication / copy-on-write
.PP
Useful for capacity planning and monitoring backup growth.
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.B SNAP_DIR
Directory containing source snapshots.
.TP
.B TARGET
Backup target: local directory path or remote
.B ssh://[user@]host[:port]/path.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-q, \-\-quiet
Suppress progress indicators and headers.
.TP
.BR \-\-log-file " \fIPATH\fR"
Write diagnostic logs to a file.
.SH OUTPUT
Tab-separated format:
.EX
snapshots	5	2.3 GB
backups	5	1.8 GB
total_size	4.1 GB
savings	450 MB
.EE
.SH EXIT CODES
.TP
.B 0
Stats retrieved successfully.
.TP
.B 1
Stats failed (e.g., directory not found).
.TP
.B 2
Usage error.
.TP
.B 4
Permission denied (requires root).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Show backup statistics:
.EX
sudo mybtrfs stats /mnt/snapshots /mnt/backup
.EE
.TP
Monitor growth over time:
.EX
date; sudo mybtrfs stats /mnt/snapshots /mnt/backup
.EE
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mybtrfs (1),
.BR mybtrfs-list (1),
.BR mybtrfs-status (1)
